Plugin developers want information about their custom fields to appear in gadgets such as Issue Statistics and Pie Chart.  They can do this by creating searchers that implement CustomFieldStattable. However they often can't render their custom field contents properly in these gadgets so the end effect looks poor.

This is because the Velocity context used to render a custom field (with the label resource) is is limited to just three variables where it is defined in CustomFieldSearcherModuleDescriptor.java getStatHtml(). Adding a line such as

{code}
Map extraVariables = field.getCustomFieldType().getVelocityParameters(null, field, null);
{code}

would at least allow extra variables to be passed when rendering the label template file. Or some other approach, but not being able to render a field's contents in a statistics gadget really holds back their use by non-Atlassian developers.

